basisset.dc:description: cc-pwCVDZ-PP core/valence relativistic small core PP basis sets --------------------------------------------------------------- Core Name Primitives Contractions Cu - Zn: 10 [Ne] ECP10MDF (9s,8p,7d,2f) -> [5s,5p,4d,2f] Ag - Cd: 28 [Ar+3d] ECP28MDF (9s,8p,7d,2f) -> [5s,5p,4d,2f] Au - Hg: 60 [Kr+4d3f] ECP60MDF (9s,8p,7d,2f) -> [5s,5p,4d,2f] Note: these basis sets are designed to be used with an active space that includes all electrons not subsumed into the pseudopotential. For example, for Cu the 3s3p3d4s electrons are correlated. Exponents from: --------------- K.A. Peterson and C. Puzzarini, Theor. Chem.
